Requirments:

Tested using Ubuntu 11.10

Hardware:
Asus Xtion Pro Live

Note: If you would like to use a MS Kinect then this *may* work out of the box.  If not (this *will* be the case if you are using the freenect driver) then please modify the code in the loadData(...) function in the file SingleFrameExtraction.cpp to use the correct load function from the nestk library.

External Libraries:
---------------------
OpenNI:
sudo apt-get install libusb-dev
install the OpenNI module first, followed by Sensor then NITE all using the install.sh scripts)

opencv 2.3.1

PCL (pointclouds.org)

Nestk (http://nicolas.burrus.name/index.php/Research/KinectUseNestk)
Simply place as a subdirectory after downloading from the authors git repo (https://github.com/nburrus/nestk)

Other dependencies:
sudo ap-get install libboost-program-options1.46-dev

Building
-----------
mkdir build
cd build
cmake ..
make


